##Spring Festival travel in the face of an epidemic: At first, no one wore a mask

Micro-signal Zairenjian11

Features, with a calm narrative against the cold | phoenix network produced in the human studio

Phoenix News Client, produced by Phoenix Network Studio on Earth

I have been recording the Spring Festival transit green trains for many years. These trains are also called "special trains for migrant workers" . They are the cheapest trains, mainly for low-income people.

As early as January 9, a friend reminded me that Wuhan has unidentified pneumonia, do not go to Wuhan this year to shoot. I didn't choose to go to or stop at Wuhan's green-skinned train, though at the time, authorities said there would be no human-to-human transmission.

This Spring Festival, I went out three times to shoot:

January 14th. First time out. At first, no one, including me, wore a mask. In three days, I've only seen a handful of people wearing masks on camera.

January 22nd, second outing. The day before, on Jan. 21, academician Zhong Nanshan confirmed that the virus had spread from person to person. The atmosphere on the train was more serious than during the Spring Festival travel rush, when about 30 percent of the people wore masks.

January 24, New Year's Eve, my third trip out the door. The day before, Wuhan had declared the city closed. I saw that most of the passengers, from the waiting room to the train, were wearing masks. From January 24 at 0:00, the Railway Department announced the exemption of refund fees. The train was not too crowded, or with many people choose not to return home for the New Year.

When shooting, I and those who do not wear a mask, did not care too much, look back, just feel a lot of emotion.

On January 14, at 12.20 am, I set foot on the linke green road from Wuxi to Fuyang. Chunyun road, red fire, accompanied by the "Chunnuanhualu" , "welcome family home" slogan.

During those days of filming, all the way, volunteers, staff, flight attendants, passengers, none of them wore masks. Apparently, no one cares about pneumonia in Wuhan, including me.

■ January 15,2020, on the 3672 Spring Festival train between Dongguan and Guang'an.
■ On the K5562 Spring Festival passenger train from Shanghai to Bozhou on January 14,2020.
■ On the 3672 Spring Festival train from Dongguan to Guang'an on January 16,2020.
■ On the K5562 Spring Festival passenger train from Shanghai to Bozhou on January 14,2020.
■ On the K5562 Spring Festival passenger train from Shanghai to Bozhou on January 14,2020.

"Dad, you've been sick, your immune system is weak, and you shouldn't be filming the Spring Festival travel shoot recently. " On January 21, when I received a call from my daughter, who works in Nanjing, the public became sensitive and nervous after the coronavirus was confirmed to have been passed from person to person.

January 22 into the Spring Festival Rush, I comfort my daughter: the Internet said no severe SARS, my father will pay attention to protection, do not worry, will be fine. I took the only three face masks I had at home and set off again.

It was impossible to say that I wasn't worried at all. I decided to give up the long-distance filming and make a two-day short trip to Xinyang and back. No, I read that I have a 2% mortality rate for coronaviruses. After all, I was born with cancer and passed through hell.

■ On the K5562 Spring Festival train from Shanghai to Bozhou on January 22,2020.

During the Spring Festival rush, the aisles of the home-bound trains are crowded with people. Under the warning that people must wear masks when they go out, only 30 percent of the people on the train are observed to be wearing masks.

Some passengers told me: "know the coronavirus, cheap life, not afraid. ". "You're too careful, " said another. "take a picture and wear a mask. ".

Long distance train, eat, drink, sleep, all on the train, the whole mask can not take off, boring, go to the Corridor connection, pull down the mask, a breath of fresh air through the window has never been sealed. At the moment, I thought to myself, sometimes it's really just luck.

On January 23, I was on the train 3218 between Xinyang and Wuxi, 200km from Wuhan, when I learned of the city's complete closure.

■ On the K5562 Spring Festival train from Shanghai to Bozhou on January 22,2020.

■ On the K5562 Spring Festival train from Shanghai to Bozhou on January 22,2020.
■ On the K5562 Spring Festival train from Shanghai to Bozhou on January 22,2020.
■ On the 8323 train from Gushi to Xinyang, on January 22,2020.
■ On the 3218 Spring Festival passenger train from Chengdu to Shanghai on January 23,2020.
■ On the 3218 Spring Festival passenger train from Chengdu to Shanghai on January 23,2020.
■ On the 3218 Spring Festival passenger train from Chengdu to Shanghai on January 23,2020.
■ On January 22,2020, the K5562 Spring Festival travel from Shanghai to Bozhou stops at Huainan station.

Spring Festival Linke Green, every year, although no sense of mission, but a long-term record, the heart will indeed produce an emotional inertia, an indescribable magic, feeling is not to go.

■ The Wuxi Railway Station, Jan. 24,2020.

January 24, New Year's Eve, I went out again with a camera, a short trip to Shanghai and back. At the moment, the train station staff are wearing masks, the station electronic screen, but also loop to teach everyone how to wear masks. The train is relatively empty to and fro, most passengers wear masks, there is no language exchange, each looking at the phone, the air seems to be frozen.

■ January 24,2020 Chengdu to Shanghai 3218 Spring Festival temporary passenger transport.
■ On the 3218 Spring Festival passenger train from Chengdu to Shanghai on January 24,2020.
■ On the 3218 Spring Festival passenger train from Chengdu to Shanghai on January 24,2020.
■ On the 3218 Spring Festival passenger train from Chengdu to Shanghai on January 24,2020.
■ On the 3218 Spring Festival passenger train from Chengdu to Shanghai on January 24,2020.
■ On the K738 train from Shanghai to Luoyang on January 24,2020.

When the crew with a mask shouted "Wuxi Station, " I got off the car to go home, the Spring Festival shooting to draw a full stop.

On January 25, the Wuxi government issued a first-level response to the epidemic.

On January 27, I saw on the Internet that there were four confirmed cases in Wuxi. Every day since then, "authoritative releases" and "latest news" have been issued, all of which are an increase in the number of confirmed cases and an increase in the level of prevention and control. It is obvious that the epidemic situation is becoming more and more serious. I can take comfort in the fact that, i have never been to Wuhan.

January 29 circle of friends to see the information about confirmed patients, I took out the ticket, one by one check, a trip did not, is a calm. Since then, the number of confirmed cases has increased, and I've been checking in.

On January 30, I received a phone call from the community asking me about my recent travels, and I told them the truth.

■ On January 31,2020, community workers went to check in.

January 31, community staff home visits, brought masks, thermometer and disinfectant and do registration, warning try not to go out, always wear a mask. I lived with my parents, and the old man was a little nervous when he saw the heavily armed community workers coming to his house. After he left, he told his mother, it's okay. The only thing I was a little uneasy about was passing through Xinyang on January 22 and having dinner at a small restaurant near the Xinyang railway station, where the boss joked that if Wuhan came, you wouldn't be allowed in.

Despite my best efforts to isolate myself, I also know that living with my parents, it is impossible to be completely out of touch, can only comfort myself: I will not be affected. Before this, I have told my daughter not to come back to see the new year grandma, told my sister not to come to see mom and dad, very little time to move around, take care of the body important.

■ On January 31,2020, community workers visited homes to bring in supplies for the epidemic.
■ A trash can delivered by a community worker on February 1,2020.

On the afternoon of February 1, the community workers came again and brought a trash can with the words "separate trash can for home use" on it.

February 2 received a phone call from the community, notice must not go out, or tell the local police station, enforced quarantine, said quarantine period from the last day back to Wuxi. At this time, the virus has spread throughout the country, very serious, home quarantine is also to ensure the safety of more people.

During the quarantine, I was keeping an eye on whether the train I was on had an updated diagnosis -- what if someone was still in the incubation period, asymptomatic, undiagnosed? This Spring Festival, I took 10 trains, to film, each train moving back and forth, when everyone is not wearing a mask, I contacted a large number of passengers, now, only time, can give me the final answer.

■ On Feb. 3,2020, a community worker brought vegetables and told them to leave at the door.

On February 3rd and 5th the community sent over the daily side dishes I needed. Home Isolation these days, I cook at home every day, was praised by my mother. The community workers call me every day to ask if I'm feeling unwell, and video-chat me, saying that there is something at home that the community can help with.

■ On February 7th, the community health workers come to my house for a physical examination, and when everything is normal, give me the medical observation notice for the release of the quarantine.
■ On Feb. 7, I asked a community worker to take a picture of me with my medical observation notice to de-quarantine at my home for a special occasion.
■ On February 8,2020, the old new village where I live, which used to have no property, now has a security guard on duty.

February 8, after many days of isolation, I went out for the first time to the supermarket shopping, only to find that I live in the 1980s, has not been the property management of the old new village, there are also security at the door, outsiders have to register to check.

I keep my train ticket for each Spring Festival travel rush. These are the 10 trains I took during this year's Spring Festival travel rush. If I had known the severity of the virus earlier, I don't know if I would have bought these ten tickets.

I hope all the passengers and staff I met on the way are well. I hope the patients who have been diagnosed will get well soon. I hope the epidemic will be over soon.
